# Workflow

## Workflow 1

Human-gated phase loop:

```text
strategy -> spec -> human approval -> Codex execution -> handoff -> Claude review -> human merge or repair
```

## Workflow 2

Provider-wired local campaign loop:

```text
campaign -> spec -> execute -> validate -> review -> repair or pass -> merge gate dry-run -> next phase
```

Supported commands:

```bash
just frontier-run-campaign <campaign>
just frontier-run-next <campaign>
just frontier-run-campaign-mock <campaign>
just frontier-run-next-mock <campaign>
just frontier-run-campaign-ledger <campaign>
just frontier-tail <run_id>
just frontier-summary <run_id>
just frontier-stop <run_id>
just frontier-resume <run_id>
```

Default semantics:

- `just frontier-run-campaign <campaign>` is aggressive campaign-loop mode.
- `FRONTIER_MAX_PHASES=1 just frontier-run-campaign <campaign>` is one-phase smoke/debug mode.
- `just frontier-run-next <campaign>` is the same one-phase smoke/debug shortcut.
- `FRONTIER_MOCK_PROVIDERS=1` or the mock just recipes use deterministic local providers and never call external CLIs.

Stop conditions:

- `STOP` file
- `BLOCKED` verdict
- validation failure
- repair exhaustion
- max phase limit
- time or CI policy block
- merge gate block

The conductor does not perform real GitHub operations, PR creation, auto-merge, deployment, live trading, paper trading, or broker actions by default.
